Sundays are for relaxing, and spending quality time with people you love. Cooking a proper beef stew for your family and friends is such a good way to bond over good food. The stew really goes well with chapati or rice. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Warm your cooking oil in a large pan over medium heat then season beef with salt and pepper, to taste. Step 2 Add beef to the pan and cook until evenly browned about 2-3 minutes. Step 3 Add your potatoes, carrots, onion, and garlic and combine Step 4 In a bowl, whisk together the beef broth, water, tomato paste, thyme, oregano, and paprika, mix until well combined; pour over the beef and cook for 10 minutes. Step 5 Add in the bay leaves and season with salt and pepper. Step 6 Cover and cook on low heat before adding your peas. Serve immediately in bowls, garnished with parsley, if desired.